<!-- ========== SECTION 5: HERBAL PROGRAM (v6) ========== -->
<section id="herbal-program">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="eyebrow">The Herbal Program</div>
    <h2>The part that turns Zuo Yue Zi from good recovery into deep recovery.</h2>

    <div class="narrow" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">
      <p class="lede" style="font-style: normal;">If you've already chosen a meal plan, you might be wondering whether you really need the herbal drinks too. It's a fair question. The meals do most of the heavy lifting — warmth, blood, milk, energy.</p>
      <p>But traditional Zuo Yue Zi was never just food. It was always food, herbs, and rest, working together. The drinks are the part that reaches the deeper layer — the joints, the circulation, the parts of recovery that matter long after the first month is over.</p>
      <p>That's why most experienced postpartum families add them. Not because the meals aren't enough. Because together is what the tradition was always meant to be.</p>

      <blockquote style="margin: 32px 0;">
        I learned this on my own body. With my first baby, I did the meals but skipped the herbs. With my second, I did both. By week 3, the difference was unmistakable — my energy came back, my milk steadied, my joints stopped aching. That's the reason this part of the program exists.
        <span class="attr">— Nicole Huang, Jing Mommy</span>
      </blockquote>
    </div>

    <h3 style="font-size: 26px; margin: 56px 0 20px;">How the drinks match your three stages of recovery</h3>
    <div class="narrow" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">
      <p>The drinks follow the same three-stage framework as the meals — Mild, Warm, and Heat — because the body does different work each week, and the herbs match it.</p>
      <p><strong>Week 1 — Mild: Cleanse and rest.</strong> Your body is still clearing lochia and resetting. The first formulas help that work happen gently, supporting circulation and internal cleansing without pushing the body before it's ready.</p>
      <p><strong>Week 2 — Warm: Replenish and rebuild.</strong> The body shifts from clearing to building. The Week 2 formulas support blood replenishment, joint and ligament recovery (your body is still reabsorbing the relaxin that loosened your joints during pregnancy), and milk supply.</p>
      <p><strong>Weeks 3–4 — Heat: Strengthen and fortify.</strong> The deepest restoration phase. The strongest tonifying formulas come last, when the body is ready to receive them. This is the layer that supports energy, mood, sleep, and the long-term warmth Chinese medicine calls protection against 月內風 (yuè nèi fēng) — the cold-sensitivity and joint pain that can follow a woman for years if this window is missed.</p>
    </div>

    <h3 style="font-size: 26px; margin: 56px 0 20px;">What's in the drinks</h3>
    <div class="narrow" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">
      <p>Across 30 days, you receive <strong>15 different formulas — a new one every two days</strong> — each matched to the stage of recovery your body is in.</p>
      <p>The core ingredients are the herbs Chinese medicine has used for postpartum recovery for centuries:</p>
      <ul class="outcomes" style="margin: 16px 0 24px 0;">
        <li><strong>Dang Gui (當歸)</strong> — traditionally used to nourish and move blood</li>
        <li><strong>Chuan Xiong (川芎)</strong> — used to support circulation and recovery from labor</li>
        <li><strong>Bai Shao (白芍)</strong> — used to calm and balance, often paired with Dang Gui</li>
        <li><strong>Shu Di (熟地)</strong> — used for deep blood replenishment</li>
        <li><strong>Huang Qi (黃耆)</strong> — used to support energy and immune function</li>
        <li>And the supporting herbs that round out each stage's formula</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This is not a single bundle brewed daily. Each of the 15 formulas is a specific combination, developed for that stage of recovery.</p>
    </div>

    <h3 style="font-size: 26px; margin: 56px 0 20px;">What mothers tell us</h3>
    <div class="narrow" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">
      <p>Within the 30-day window, here's what mothers on the herbal drinks come back to tell us most often:</p>
      <ul class="outcomes" style="margin: 16px 0 24px 0;">
        <li>They feel like themselves again sooner — the fog lifts, the energy returns, and it happens earlier than they expected</li>
        <li>Their milk supply holds steady, even through the exhausting weeks</li>
        <li>They sleep better and feel more even, with less of the emotional crash</li>
        <li>The aches, the chill, and the night sweats settle down</li>
        <li>And the one mothers value most only shows up later: none of the lingering cold-sensitivity and joint pain (月內風) that Chinese medicine warns follows an incomplete recovery</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="font-style: italic; color: var(--muted);">Time and again, these are the patterns we hear from mothers who do the full program — not guarantees, but consistent enough that we mention them with confidence.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="herbal-pricing" style="margin: 56px 0 32px;">
      <h4>How to Get the Herbal Drinks</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Included free</strong> in every Herbal Meal plan — fresh and frozen. The full 30-day course of drinks, no add-on cost.</li>
        <li><strong>Add to a fresh meal plan — {usd(products.herbal_drink.price)}/day.</strong> Available with Classic, Vita, Low Carb, or Easy plans.</li>
        <li><strong>Add to a frozen meal plan — {usd(products.frozen_herbal_drink_7_1w.price)}/week.</strong> Available with Classic, Vita, or Soup &amp; Dessert plans.</li>
        <li><strong>{usd(products.herbal_drink_pack_30d.price)} standalone Herbal Pack.</strong> For the mom who has home-cooked meals covered, but doesn't want to miss the herbal layer of Zuo Yue Zi. Ships nationwide.</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="#herbal-program" class="plan-link sans" style="margin-top: 20px; display: inline-block;">Learn more about the herbal drinks →</a>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

