<!-- ========== SECTION 7: FAQ ========== -->
<section class="alt">
  <div class="narrow">
    <div class="eyebrow">Frequently Asked</div>
    <h2>Questions other mothers have asked.</h2>
    <p class="lede">These are real questions our team answers every day. If yours isn't here, call us at {phoneDisplay(phones.main)}.</p>

    <details class="faq" open>
      <summary>Can I skip organ meats like liver and kidneys?</summary>
      <div class="answer">Organ meats carry specific nutritional value during recovery — that's why they've been part of Zuo Yue Zi for centuries. If you're hesitant, the broth itself still delivers much of the same benefit, so we'd encourage you to try the broth even if you skip the meat. If you can't eat them at all, we can substitute — but the more we substitute, the less variety your menu will have over thirty days. Just tell us when you order.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq">
      <summary>I'm not Chinese. Is Zuo Yue Zi for me?</summary>
      <div class="answer">The principles behind Zuo Yue Zi — warmth, rest, targeted nourishment in stages — aren't culturally exclusive. They're biological. Your body recovers from birth the same way regardless of which tradition you grew up with. What's different is that one tradition has been refining the answer for over 2,000 years.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq">
      <summary>What if the food tastes too unfamiliar?</summary>
      <div class="answer">This is exactly why we offer a tasting first. Most mothers expecting strange flavors are surprised by how warming and comforting the food actually is. Order the {usd(products.local_classic_sample_1d.price)} Local Tasting if you're in our Southern California delivery area, or the {usd(products.frozen_classic_sample_8item.price)} Frozen Tasting if you're not. If the food's not for you, you'll know before committing to a plan.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq">
      <summary>Can my partner and family eat the meals too?</summary>
      <div class="answer">Our meals are designed for one — the new mother. Many of our customers tell us the portions are large enough that their partner ends up sharing, but we can't promise it. If you want enough food for both of you, the safer answer is to add a Daddy Meal or order a second portion. We'd rather be honest than have you run out three days in.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq">
      <summary>I had a C-section or a difficult birth — does that change anything?</summary>
      <div class="answer">All our plans use the same recovery food — including the warming, iron-replenishing dishes that line up well with C-section healing. The difference is the daily herbal drinks, which work alongside the food at a deeper level over the full thirty days. Many C-section moms choose the Herbal Meal for that reason. Choose the plan that fits when you order, and you can always adjust later.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq">
      <summary>What if I'm not breastfeeding?</summary>
      <div class="answer">We'll remove the milk-stimulating ingredients from your menu. The food still does its main job — restoring blood, warmth, and energy after birth. The one thing to know: removing those ingredients means fewer dishes in rotation, so the menu can feel slightly more repetitive.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq">
      <summary>I'm outside your fresh delivery zone — how does shipping work?</summary>
      <div class="answer">Frozen meals ship via FedEx Priority Overnight, packed in thermal packaging with ice packs. Each day's meals come pre-portioned into a single thermal bag — grab one bag, that's your day. We ship to the continental US (not Alaska or Hawaii). If your freezer is small, you can pick up a small upright freezer or keep 5 days frozen and 2 days thawing in the fridge.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq">
      <summary>When should I order if my due date isn't set yet?</summary>
      <div class="answer">Over 90% of orders come in before the due date — most mothers want one less thing to worry about. We recommend placing your order at least a month before your due date so we can hold a slot. Once the baby arrives, just let us know — your meals start whenever you notify us, not on a fixed calendar.</div>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

